The terms 'Visual Programming' and 'Program Visualization' have been applied to these systems. This paper attempts to provide more meaning to these terms by giving precise definitions, and then surveys a number of systems that can be classified as providing Visual Programming or Program Visualization. These systems are organized by classifying them into three different taxonomies

[2021/2/16-10:57-clip]	 	new BuffDefinition({
		identifier: BuffIdentifier.Stun,
		duration: 1000,
		startingStacks: 1,
		stackStyle: StackStyle.RollingStackDurationSeparately,
		reapplyStacks: 1,
		reapplyDuration: 1000,
		applyFn: (buff: Buff) => {
			let movementSpeedBuff = 0
			let attackRateBuff = 0

			if (buff.appliedTo instanceof ServerPlayer) {
				movementSpeedBuff = -0.3
				attackRateBuff = -0.3
			} else if (buff.appliedTo.enemyType === EnemyType.BOSS) {
				movementSpeedBuff = -0.3
				attackRateBuff = -0.3
			} else {
				// normal enemies and champions
				movementSpeedBuff = -1
				attackRateBuff = -1
			}

			buff.state = {
				bonus1: buff.appliedTo.statList.addStatBonus('movementSpeed', StatOperatorType.MULTIPLY, movementSpeedBuff),
				bonus2: buff.appliedTo.statList.addStatBonus('attackRate', StatOperatorType.MULTIPLY, attackRateBuff),
			}
		},
		wearOffFn: (buff: Buff) => {
			buff.state.bonus1.remove()
			buff.state.bonus2.remove()
		},
		showToClient: true,
	}),

[2021/2/16-14:18-clip]	 	static getInstance(params?: any): NengiClient {
		if (!NengiClient.instance) {
			if (params === undefined) {
				throw new Error('No nengi params given to NengiClient getInstance(); aborting startup')
			} else {
				NengiClient.instance = new NengiClient(params.nengiConfig, params.interpDelay)
			}
		}

		return NengiClient.instance
	}

[2021/2/17-20:41-tab]	 #loot-game-design - Discord
[2021/2/17-20:42-clip]	 const dodgeRollConfig = {
    inputMovementPreventedDurationMultiplier: 0.72,
    attackCooldownMultiplier: 0.7,
    physicsForce1: {
        durationMultiplier: 0.6,
        accelerationMultiplier: 0.6,
    },
    physicsForce2: {
        durationMultiplier: 0.8,
        accelerationMultiplier: 0.4,
    },
}
export function performDodgeRoll(player: ServerPlayer, slot: CooldownSlot, movement: Vector, acceleration: number) {
    const skillDurationMs: timeInMilliseconds = getSkillDurationMs(player, slot)
    const skillDurationSeconds = skillDurationMs * 0.001
    const skillSpeed = player.getGearSlotPlusBaseStat(slot, 'skillSpeed')
    player.inputMovementPrevented = skillDurationSeconds * dodgeRollConfig.inputMovementPreventedDurationMultiplier
    console.log(`inputMovementPrevented: ${player.inputMovementPrevented}`, dodgeRollConfig)
    player.addOrKeepAttackCooldown(skillDurationSeconds * dodgeRollConfig.attackCooldownMultiplier)
    Buff.apply(BuffIdentifier.NoCollideWithProjectile, player, player, 1, skillDurationMs)
    player.velocity.x = 0
    player.velocity.y = 0

    const force1 = new ExternalPhysicsForce(movement.clone().scale(acceleration * skillSpeed * dodgeRollConfig.physicsForce1.accelerationMultiplier), dodgeRollConfig.physicsForce1.durationMultiplier * skillDurationSeconds, null, true)
    player.externalForces.push(force1)
    const force2 = new ExternalPhysicsForce(movement.clone().scale(acceleration * skillSpeed * dodgeRollConfig.physicsForce2.accelerationMultiplier), dodgeRollConfig.physicsForce2.durationMultiplier * skillDurationSeconds, null, false)
    player.externalForces.push(force2)
}
DevToolsManager.getInstance().addObjectByName('dodgeRollConfig', { closure: dodgeRollConfig })

[2021/2/19-10:19-clip]	 client: Client, args: string
[2021/2/19-10:19-input]	 cv
[2021/2/19-10:19-clip]	 		let worldX = 1
		let worldY = 1
		let allArgs = args.split(' ')
		if (allArgs.length === 1) {
			allArgs = args.split(',')
		}
		if (allArgs.length) {
			if (allArgs.length >= 1) {
				worldX = Number.parseInt(allArgs[0], 10)
			}
			if (allArgs.length >= 2) {
				worldY = Number.parseInt(allArgs[1], 10)
			}
			if (isNaN(worldX) || isNaN(worldY)) {
				this.sendChatMessage(client, `You messed up the syntax! Shame on you!`)
				this.showHelp(client, args)
				return
			}
		}

		worldX = Math.clamp(worldX, 1, WORLD_WIDTH)
		worldY = Math.clamp(worldY, 1, WORLD_HEIGHT)

		client.entity.moveTo(worldX, worldY)
		this.sendChatMessage(client, `Teleported to world ${worldX},${worldY}`)

[2021/2/19-13:6-clip]	 function debounce( callback, delay ) {
    let timeout;
    return function() {
        clearTimeout( timeout );
        timeout = setTimeout( callback, delay );
    }
}
